Asia Remains ‘Greatly Exposed’ to Global Contagion, Singh Says

-- B y   S h a m i m   A d a m
-- 
2011-09-24T14:17:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-24/asia-remains-greatly-exposed-to-global-contagion-singh-says.html
Asian nations remain “greatly
exposed” to global contagion, Anoop Singh, director of the
Asia-Pacific department at the International Monetary Fund, said
today. In a news conference in  Washington , Singh said
overheating pressures remain in  Asia .   To contact the reporter on this story:
